Comments. Originally described based on three specimens from a single locality in the Northern Western Ghats (
Giri et al . 2019
). Our study has expanded the morphological and geographical boundary of this species, by examining a ten-fold higher number of specimens (n=33) from sites spanning over 1300 km , across the entire Western Ghats. We also depict its phylogenetic placement in a tree for the first time; in addition to genetic distances (also see
Giri et al . 2019
).
